# Build & verify

## When this applies

User asks to **build**, **verify**, **check compilation**, or after edits that might break the **excalidraw-app** / **packages** build.

## Required workflow

1. From **repository root**, run **`yarn build`** (see `AGENTS.md`).
2. On **success:** report **PASS**, note touched areas, include **full** build output (or last run’s complete log).
3. On **failure:** read errors (file, line, type vs syntax), fix **source** (types, imports, exports), re-run **`yarn build`**.
4. Stop after **3** failed fix cycles; report **FAIL**, paste full output, summarize blockers.

## How to verify

- From the **repo root**, **`yarn build`** exits with code **0** and no unresolved compilation errors.
- The reported **PASS** matches the terminal; if the log was truncated, re-run and confirm the same result.
- Fixes did **not** introduce **`@ts-ignore`**, **`@ts-expect-error`**, or **`any`** solely to silence errors.
- Optionally run **`yarn test:typecheck`** when the change touches TypeScript types.

## Forbidden shortcuts

- No **`@ts-ignore`**, **`@ts-expect-error`**, or **`any`** just to silence errors.
- Do not weaken **tests** or skip assertions to green the build — fix production code or types.
- Do not change **test files** only to mask production breakage (unless the test itself is wrong).
